&lt;h1&gt;Continuous Improvement Education Lead (Delivering Excellence)&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;If you have a passion for improving services through the development, coaching and education of others, and want to play a pivotal part in implementing continuous improvement across an organsation, then wew would love you to join us!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;At Portsmouth we’ve been working hard to improve our care for our patients and our communities and are proud of achieving a “Good” CQC rating.  But we don’t want to stop there. Our Trust vision is &lt;em&gt;Working together to drive excellence in care for our patients and communities&lt;/em&gt;. To achieve excellence, we know we need to develop our  Trust-wide approach to managing our quality through continuous improvement of our day-to-day actions, functions, and processes - and through the engagement and enthusiasm of our staff. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;We’ve already made a start on our &lt;em&gt;Delivering Excellence&lt;/em&gt; system and have invested in a core team to develop and embed our approach.  &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Continuous Improvement (CI) Education Lead will be a senior member of the Delivering Excellence core team and will take responsibility for building capability and capacity for improvement within the Trust.  The role will lead the design and delivery of continuous learning and development opportunities for all Trust staff to support the implementation and sustainability of the Delivering Excellence approach.  The post-holder will design an education and continuous learning framework that builds the skills, knowledge and competencies at the level and capacity required to support successful adoption and embedding of the Delivering Excellence approach within the organisation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;A background in healthcare is not essential, but the experience of working across a complex organisation in the field of continuous improvement is.&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Interview date: Monday 7 December 2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 18th November 2020&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
